-- Samsung Elec sees 2007 global LCD market up 22 pct
-- 
-- Thu Jan 11, 2007 9:37pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/01/12/us-samsung-lcds-forecast-idUSSP19595920070112

 

 SEOUL  (Reuters) - Samsung Electronics Co. Ltd. ( 005930.KS ) forecast on Friday the global liquid crystal display (LCD) panel market would rise 22 percent from a year ago in terms of units sold, with prices seen falling slightly. 

 "The market for 2007 is expected to continue growing, led by large-sized panels," Samsung said in presentation material filed to the regulatory Financial Supervisory Service. It expected the global shipment of LCD panels to come to 324 million units this year.